05/07/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Interior Minister Vasile Blaga met with his visiting Croatian counterpart, Marijan Mlinaric, on Monday (4 July) and agreed to boost bilateral co-operation in the fight against organised crime, trafficking and illegal migration.
During the talks, Blaga also reaffirmed Bucharest's support for Zagreb's efforts to join the EU and NATO.
In other news Monday, Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu visited Israel, where he met with counterpart Silvan Shalom.
They focused on boosting bilateral ties and on the Middle East peace process.
(Nine o'clock, Rompres - 04/07/05)
